#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/installova.rst:3
msgid "Installing OPNsense OVA image"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/installova.rst:5
msgid ""
"OPNsense is available as an Open Virtual Appliance (OVA) package, which "
"can be deployed in various virtualization products (e.g. VMWare, "
"Virtualbox)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/installova.rst:8
msgid ""
"The image is not provided as a community free download, but can be "
"acquired from Deciso."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/installova.rst:10
msgid ""
"In this document we describe the simple steps when deploying in "
"VirtualBox, other supported platforms function quite similar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/installova.rst:15
msgid "Step 1 - Import appliance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/installova.rst:17
msgid ""
"In the top menu, choose :menuselection:`File --> Import appliance` and "
"select the image you downloaded, it should show a dialog like the "
"following."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/installova.rst:23
msgid ""
"Just click import, accept the license and the image should be transferred"
" to your machine."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/installova.rst:28
msgid "Step 2 - Network setup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/installova.rst:30
msgid ""
"The OVA template comes with two interfaces configured by default (you can"
" add more later if needed). Always choose the right type of network "
"before using OPNsense, the imported adapters might not be assigned to a "
"type after import."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/installova.rst:36
msgid ""
"Please be aware that the order of the network cards in the virtualization"
" product may differ from how they are presented to the operating system. "
"In VirtualBox \"Adapter 1\" seems to connect to WAN (em1)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/installova.rst:42
msgid "Step 3 - Initial configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/installova.rst:44
msgid ""
"The virtual machine is operational now, initial configuration is "
"performed similar to other setups, as described in :doc:`../install`."
msgstr ""

